## When to use
Use this skill when you need detailed information about your system's disk input/output operations. This is particularly useful for monitoring and diagnosing issues related to disk performance.

## Approach
Utilize the `shell_exec` tool in KDEV to run the `iostat -dx 1` command, which provides interval-based reports of I/O statistics by disk device. This will allow you to monitor disk activity over time and analyze any potential bottlenecks or issues.

## Example
```shell
shell_exec('iostat -dx 1')
```

## Pitfalls
- Ensure the `sysstat` package is installed on your system as `iostat` may not be available by default.
- Be aware that continuous monitoring with high frequency (e.g., every second) can slightly affect system performance and disk I/O metrics.